<subSubSection id="C305C2C0752FFFDADFD8FC67FD3A12E4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA0914B752FFFDADFD8FC67FC8913A0" blockId="2.[151,1436,1009,1501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
DESCRIPTION: Shell medium to large (adult length 
<quantity id="4CE73CAE752FFFDADDB6FC67FC7D1330" box="[761,901,1009,1033]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.125" metricValueMax="1.85" metricValueMin="0.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="112.5" valueMax="185.0" valueMin="40.0">40–185 mm</quantity>
), fusiform with high spire and long, unnotched siphonal canal; anal sinus a deep slot situated on a ridge immediately above the peripheral keel; sculpture of spiral cords or ridges, sinus cord often crenulated. Usually with brown spots or stripes. Protoconch usually minute and papilliform, of 
<number id="3DD7836C752FFFDADE06FBCBFE8B134C" box="[329,371,1117,1141]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5</number>
whorls, smooth, later whorls usually axially ribbed; in some species large and bulbous, of 
<number id="3DD7836C752FFFDADFD8FB17FF4013A0" box="[151,184,1153,1177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.5">1.5</number>
–2.0 smooth whorls. Operculum ungulate, typical of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FEAC8752FFFDADC45FB17FC9513A0" box="[778,877,1153,1177]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Turrinae">Turrinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA0914B752FFFDADF88FB33FDC113D8" blockId="2.[151,1436,1009,1501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Radula of duplex marginal teeth, varying considerably in shape, sometimes with a quadrate central tooth bearing a small to large median cusp.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA0914B752FFFDADF88FB78FB3A1210" blockId="2.[151,1436,1009,1501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName id="4C1FEAC8752FFFDADF88FB78FEF3123C" authorityName="Batsch" authorityYear="1789" box="[199,267,1262,1285]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Turris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96B4D59752FFFDADF88FB78FEF3123C" box="[199,267,1262,1285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Turris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a tropical Indo-West Pacific group with only one temperate water species (the South African 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FEAC8752FFFDADA18FB78FE681210" authority="Kilburn, 1998" authorityName="Kilburn" authorityYear="1998" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Turris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="faleiroi">
<emphasis id="B96B4D59752FFFDADA18FB78FF111210" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Turris faleiroi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EECBA752FFFDADFA0FA87FE681210" author="Kilburn" box="[239,400,1297,1321]" firstAuthor="Kilburn" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="155 - 160" refId="ref31100" refString="Kilburn, R. N. (1998) Description of four new neogastropods of superfamilies Muricoidea and Conoidea from South Africa. Apex, 13 (4), 155 - 160." type="journal article" year="1998">
Kilburn, 
<number id="3DD7836C752FFFDADE1BFA87FE681210" box="[340,400,1297,1321]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). No species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FEAC8752FFFDADD0CFA84FD7F1210" authorityName="Batsch" authorityYear="1789" box="[579,647,1298,1321]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Turris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96B4D59752FFFDADD0CFA84FD7F1210" box="[579,647,1298,1321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Turris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur in the Atlantic Ocean or Mediterranean Sea.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA0914B752FFFDADF88FAA3FD3A12E4" blockId="2.[151,1436,1009,1501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FEAC8752FFFDADE0AFAA0FE711274" authorityName="Batsch" authorityYear="1789" box="[325,393,1334,1357]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Turris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96B4D59752FFFDADE0AFAA0FE711274" box="[325,393,1334,1357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Turris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was distinguished by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EECBA752FFFDADDC5FAA3FCDD1274" author="Powell" box="[650,805,1333,1357]" firstAuthor="Powell" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="227 - 346" refId="ref32010" refString="Powell, A. W. B. (1964) The family Turridae in the Indo-Pacific. Part 1. The subfamily Turrinae. Indo-Pacific Mollusca, 1 (5), 227 - 346, pls 172 - 262." type="journal article" year="1964">Powell (1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EECBA752FFFDADC7DFAA3FC941274" author="Powell" box="[818,876,1333,1357]" firstAuthor="Powell" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 184" refId="ref32052" refString="Powell, A. W. B. (1966) The molluscan families Speightiidae and Turridae an evaluation of the valid taxa, both Recent and fossil, with lists of characteristic species. Bulletin of the Auckland Institute and Museum, 5, 1 - 184." type="journal article" year="1966">1966</bibRefCitation>
) from the very similar genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FEAC8752FFFDADB8DFAA3FF2A1248" authority="Casey, 1904" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1904" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Lophiotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96B4D59752FFFDADB8DFAA3FAB21274" box="[1218,1354,1333,1357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Lophiotoma</emphasis>
Casey, 
<number id="3DD7836C752FFFDADFD8FACFFF2A1248" box="[151,210,1369,1393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</taxonomicName>
, on the basis of the anal sinus being situated on a ”special” spiral cord, not on the peripheral cord as in the latter. This convention is followed here, although this difference hinges solely on the relative strength of the two cords, a character not always clearly defined. We follow 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EECBA752FFFDADC63FA37FC201280" author="Li &amp; Li" box="[812,984,1441,1465]" firstAuthor="Li" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="63 - 68" refId="ref31490" refString="Li, Baoquan &amp; Li, Xinzheng (2007) An account of the Genus Turris species (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Turridae) from the East and South China Seas. Zootaxa, 1397, 63 - 68." type="journal article" year="2007">
Li &amp; Li (
<number id="3DD7836C752FFFDADCDAFA37FC281280" box="[917,976,1441,1465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2007.0">2007</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
in leaving the status of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FEAC8752FFFDADBA1FA37FA851280" authorityName="Powell" authorityYear="1966" box="[1262,1405,1441,1465]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Annulaturris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96B4D59752FFFDADBA1FA37FA851280" box="[1262,1405,1441,1465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Annulaturris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in abeyance, pending more extensive radula studies.
</paragraph>
